==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Phase splitter
<hw>Phase splitter</hw>. <fld>(Elec.)</fld> <def>A device by which a
single-phase current is split into two or more currents differing in
phase. It is used in starting single-phase induction motors.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Phase splitting</ent>⟦br⟧
